# POS product isolation

## Restaurant POS (frozen for new features)

- Frontend: `frontend/features/pos/`
- Routes: `/pos/*`
- Backend: `backend/src/modules/phase-3-sales-receivables/pos/`
- API: `/api/pos/*`

Only bugfixes unless the user explicitly asks for restaurant POS changes.

## Market POS (new work)

- Frontend: `frontend/features/pos-market/`
- Routes: `/pos-market/*`
- Backend: `backend/src/modules/phase-3-sales-receivables/pos-market/`
- API: `/api/pos-market/*`

All new market/retail POS features go here.

## Shared layer

- `frontend/features/pos-shared` — hooks/helpers used by both products
- `frontend/lib/api` — HTTP fetchers (`/pos/*`, `/pos-market/*`, inventory, etc.)

## Hard rules

- Never import `features/pos` from `features/pos-market` or the reverse.
- Both products may import `features/pos-shared` and `lib/api`.
- `pos-shared` must not import `features/pos` or `features/pos-market`.
- Never add market flows to `pos-page.tsx`.
- Never add restaurant table/kitchen/delivery flows to `pos-market`.
- Shared UI primitives (`components/ui`) and ERP modules (inventory, accounting) may be reused.
- Update `docs/pos-market/README.md` when market POS structure or behavior changes.
